Analyze Your Data

As a best practice in CRM Analytics, catch mistakes early by reviewing the results of each node and transformation that you add to a Data Prep recipe.

REQUIRED USER PERMISSIONS
To create a recipe:	Edit CRM Analytics Dataflows OR Edit Dataset Recipes

The preview shows a sample of the dataâ€”up to 5,000 rows. It shows the latest available data, except when you preview a connected object. When previewing a connected object, the preview might show outdated sample data.

In the Data Prep recipe, select a node in the graph to view its results. Selecting an Aggregate node or Filter node will show the corresponding preview results.

Subsequent nodes apply their logic to the sample. This behavior means that the sample set can become empty if the input sample rows don't have IDs in common or if a filter's criteria removes all the sample rows.

To ensure correct results, edit the node or transformation as needed. When the data preview doesn't complete immediately, view the preview build status at a glance with the progress wheel.

To focus on columns that are impacted by a node or transformation, hide a column from the preview or view the columns only and hide the data.

To save the recipe, click Save.

To increase performance when previewing results in Data Prep, hide columns that don't require a preview. You can also disable data preview if it's still delayed.

To further increase preview performance, hide all unused columns.

Watch a Demo:  Preview Recipe Changes to Data (English Only)
title: Previewing Results in Data Prep Recipe
